==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|xno|en}} / {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|mercurial}}, and their source, {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|mercurialis}}, from {{m|la|Mercurius||Mercury}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/məːˈkjʊəɹɪəl/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/mɝˈkjʊɹi.əl/|/mɝˈkjɔɹi.əl/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete}} Any of the [[plant]]s known as [[mercury]]. {{defdate|13th-17th c.}}
# {{lb|en|astrology}} Someone born under the influence of [[Mercury]]. {{defdate|from 16th c.}}
# {{lb|en|now|_|historical}} A preparation of mercury, especially as a treatment for [[syphilis]]. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}

